track_notes: The quickest route to the summit is from Powderface Trail, the gravel road running from Hwy 66 to Hwy 68. The road is closed from Dec 1st to May 14th. The parking spot for about 8 cars is 6km north of the start of gravel from Hwy 66 at the top of a pass. The well used and clearly defined trail leads easily to a pass at about 2020m asl. There is a map at this point, indicating the trail leading SE up through the trees, eventually rising above the tree line and running parallel to the summit ridge on the west side. Choose your point to climb to the ridge itself, for great views east towards Calgary on the horizon. Bell cell-phone coverage is available on the summit.

Park at the Elbow Falls trailhead before the winter road closure gate.  Walk through the closed gate to the Powderace Creek Trail and follow it to the secondary trail headed in the direction of Powderface Ridge.  At a Col, leave this secondary trail and bushwhack up the ridge.  Once you have gained the summit ridge, it is a straight forward beautiful walk along the ridge to the summit.

The trailhead is in a pull-off at the summit of Hwy 66 and it is only accessible between May 15th and Nov 30th as Hwy 66 is closed in winter.
The trail is well-defined and constructed, and a pleasure to hike.
